---
layout: base.njk
title: Read
description: Original writing, the events calendar, and the best reporting and research on expiring affordability.
permalink: /read/
---
<header class="hero">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="eyebrow">Read</div>
    <h1>Writing, events, and the <span>best of everyone else's</span>.</h1>
    <p class="deck">
      Everything here is sourced and every source is named. Where a number is contested, we say so.
    </p>
  </div>
</header>

<main class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="cards">
      <a class="card" href="/articles/">
        <div class="meta">Original</div>
        <h3>Articles</h3>
        <p>Analysis and dispatches, written by tenants living through it.</p>
        <div class="more">{{ collections.articles.length }} published →</div>
      </a>
      <a class="card" href="/events/">
        <div class="meta">In person</div>
        <h3>Events</h3>
        <p>Rallies, screenings, trainings, art builds. Organizing happens in rooms. Send us yours and we'll list it.</p>
        <div class="more">See what's on →</div>
      </a>
      <a class="card" href="/reading/">
        <div class="meta">Elsewhere</div>
        <h3>Reading list</h3>
        <p>The best reporting and research on LIHTC expiration, with a note on why each piece matters. Nobody had made this list, so we made it.</p>
        <div class="more">{{ links.length }} links →</div>
      </a>
    </div>

    {% if collections.articles.length %}
    <div style="margin-top:64px">
      <div class="eyebrow dark">Latest</div>
      <div class="cards" style="margin-top:20px">
        {% for post in collections.articles | limit(3) %}
        <a class="card" href="{{ post.url }}">
          <div class="meta">{{ post.data.tag or "Article" }} · {{ post.data.date | readableDate }}</div>
          <h3>{{ post.data.title }}</h3>
          <p>{{ post.data.description }}</p>
          <div class="more">Read →</div>
        </a>
        {% endfor %}
      </div>
    </div>
    {% endif %}
  </div>
</main>
